Package com.google.gxp.compiler.base

Interface Summary
Callable Something that can be "called", eg: with a <call:*> element.
CallableVisitor<T> Visitor that distinguishes between regular Callables, and InstanceCallables.
CallVisitor<T> Visitor for Calls.
ExpressionVisitor<T> Visitor for Expressions.
Implementable Represents an interface created in gxp.
ImplementsVisitor<T> Visitor for ImplementsDeclarations
ImportVisitor<T> Visitor for Imports.
InstanceCallable A Callable that requires a "this" parameter which is the object in which the method being called lives.
Node An artifact generated from some source code.
OutputLanguageVisitor<K,V> Visitor for OutputLanguages.
Root A Node that can be the Root of a GXP document.
RootVisitor<T> Visitor for Roots.
TypeVisitor<T> Visitor for Types.
 

Class Summary
AbbrExpression A Expression that declares a variable ("abbreviation").
AbstractCallable Straightforward abstract implementation of Callable.
AbstractNode Straightforward abstract implementation of Node.
AbstractRoot<T extends AbstractRoot> An abstract implementation of Root.
AttrBundleParam An Expression representing an Attribute Bundle as a parameter being passed in to a call.
AttrBundleReference An Expression representing a reference to an attribute bundle.
AttributeName The (name-space-qualified) name of an XML attribute.
BooleanConstant An Expression representing a constant boolean value (true or false)
BooleanType The boolean type.
BoundCall Represents a call that has been bound to the Callable that it calls.
BoundImplementsDeclaration Represents a declaration that the enclosing template implements an Implementable; BoundImplementsDeclarations are "bound" because they have a reference to the Implementable object referenced by the declaration
BundleType The bundle type.
Call A call.
ClassImport A GXP class import.
CollapseExpression A value that indicates that its subexpression is eligible for space collapsing.
Concatenation An Expression which concatenates other Expressions together.
Conditional A conditional Expression.
Conditional.Clause Every condition that has to be checked is a Clause.
ConstructedConstant A ConstructedConstant is a string that will be converted into an object by a function implemented by the callee.
Constructor A template constructor.
ContentType Types that correspond to MIME content types.
ConvertibleToContent Prior to the binding phase, indicates that an Expression can be converted to content.
CppFileImport A C++ File Import.
CppLibraryImport A C++ Library Import.
DefaultingExpressionVisitor<T> Abstract base class useful for creating implementations of ExpressionVisitor that do the same thing for almost all types of Expression.
DefaultingImportVisitor<T> Abstract base class useful for creating implementations of ImportVisitor that do the same thing for almost all types of Import.
DefaultingTypeVisitor<T> Abstract base class useful for creating implementations of TypeVisitor that do the same thing for almost all types of Type.
EscapeExpression An expression which "escapes" a subexpression.
ExampleExpression An Expression that has been decorated with an example suitable for use in a Placeholder
ExceptionExpression An Expression that throws an Exception at runtime.
ExhaustiveExpressionVisitor An abstract base class useful for implementing the typical type of RootVisitor/ExpressionVisitor that transforms certain kinds of Nodes, while leaving other types of Nodes (mostly) alone.
ExhaustiveRootVisitor An abstract base class useful for implementing the typical type of RootVisitor that transforms certain kinds of Nodes, while leaving other types of Nodes (mostly) alone.
Expression A node that can (eventually) be evaluated.
ExtractedMessage A <gxp:msg> that has been "extracted" by the com.google.gxp.compiler.msgextract.MessageExtractor MessageExtractor.
Forest<E extends Node> A forest of Node trees.
FormalParameter A GXP parameter.
FormalTypeParameter A GXP formal type parameter.
ImplementsDeclaration A GXP implements.
Import A GXP import.
InstanceType A Type that refers to an instantiated GXP template.
Interface A GXP interface.
IsXmlExpression Expression used to distinguish SGML vs XML mode
JavaAnnotation A Node representing a Java Annotation.
LoopExpression A looping Expression.
MultiLanguageAttrValue An attribute that can be specified with varying language namespace prefixes to indicated that different values should be used for different OutputLanguages.
NativeExpression A native (that is, in the output language) expression.
NativeImplementsDeclaration Represents a declaration that the enclosing template implements a native language (commonly java) interface.
NativeType Native types are essentially black-boxes as far as GXP is concerned.
NoMessage Internal representation of a <gxp:nomsg> element.
NullRoot A null Root.
ObjectConstant ObjectConstant is a constant String that will be converted into an object when used as a parameter for a call
OutputElement Represents an element in the output format.
PackageImport A GXP class import.
Parameter A GXP parameter.
PlaceholderEnd Internal representation of <gxp:eph>, prior to execution of PlaceholderPivoter.
PlaceholderNode Internal representation of <gxp:ph>/<gxp:eph> pair.
PlaceholderStart Internal representation of <gxp:ph>, prior to execution of PlaceholderPivoter.
SerializableAbstractNode Straightforward serializable implementation of Node.
SpaceOperatorSet A set of space operators.
StringConstant A Expression that can be evaluated at compile time.
Template A GXP template.
TemplateName The name of a template.
TemplateName.FullyQualified A fully qualified TemplateName.
TemplateType A Type that refers to an GXP template with static methods.
ThrowsDeclaration Internal representation of a <gxp:throws> element.
Tree<E extends Root> A Forest, but with only one child: the "root".
Type A Node representing a type.
UnboundCall Represents a call that has not (yet) been bound to the Callable that it calls.
UnboundImplementsDeclaration Represents a declaration that the enclosing template implements an Implementable; UnboundImplementsDeclarations are "unbound" because a TemplateName for the Implementable is known, but it is unknown whether an Implementable with that TemplateName exists.
UnextractedMessage A <gxp:msg> that has not yet been "extracted" by the com.google.gxp.compiler.msgextract.MessageExtractor MessageExtractor.
Util Utility functions for things that are done frequently in the GXP compiler.
ValidatedCall Represents a call that has been "validated".
